The paper deals with a geometric game involving points in $\mathbb{R}^d$, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem involves selecting points that satisfy certain conditions, which is a common theme in discrete optimization (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the computational complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
